hh3cL2VpnPwe3.name: hh3cL2VpnPwe3
hh3cL2VpnPwe3.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cL2VpnPwe3.description: This MIB contains objects to manage PWE3.

Hh3cL2VpnVcEncapsType.name: Hh3cL2VpnVcEncapsType
Hh3cL2VpnVcEncapsType.description: An indication of the L2Vpn's VC encapsulation type: Frame Relay DLCI ( Martini Mode ) (1) ATM AAL5 SDU VCC transport (2) ATM transparent cell transport (3) Ethernet Tagged Mode (4) Ethernet (5) HDLC (6) PPP (7) SONET/SDH Circuit Emulation Service Over MPLS (CEM) (8) ATM n-to-one VCC cell transport (9) ATM n-to-one VPC cell transport (10) IP Layer2 Transport (11) ATM one-to-one VCC Cell Mode (12) ATM one-to-one VPC Cell Mode (13) ATM AAL5 PDU VCC transport (14) Frame-Relay Port mode (15) SONET/SDH Circuit Emulation over Packet (CEP) (16) Structure-agnostic E1 over Packet (SAE1oP) (17) Structure-agnostic T1 (DS1) over Packet (SAT1oP) (18) Structure-agnostic E3 over Packet (SAE3oP) (19) Structure-agnostic T3 (DS3) over Packet (SAT3oP) (20) CESoPSN basic mode (21) TDMoIP basic mode (22) CESoPSN TDM with CAS (23) TDMoIP TDM with CAS (24) Frame Relay DLCI (25) IP-interworking (64) unknown (255)

hh3cPwVcTrapOpen.name: hh3cPwVcTrapOpen
hh3cPwVcTrapOpen.description: Whether pwe3 trap is globally enabled. false: disable; true: enable.

hh3cPwVcTable.name: hh3cPwVcTable
hh3cPwVcTable.description: This table is the VC configuration table. Users can create or delete a VC by it.

hh3cPwVcEntry.name: hh3cPwVcEntry
hh3cPwVcEntry.description: Provides the information of a VC entry.

hh3cPwVcIndex.name: hh3cPwVcIndex
hh3cPwVcIndex.description: Index for the conceptual row identifying a PW within this PW Emulation table.

hh3cPwVcID.name: hh3cPwVcID
hh3cPwVcID.description: Used in the outgoing PW ID field within the 'Virtual Circuit FEC Element'.

hh3cPwVcType.name: hh3cPwVcType
hh3cPwVcType.description: Indication of the L2Vpn's VC encapsulation type.

hh3cPwVcPeerAddr.name: hh3cPwVcPeerAddr
hh3cPwVcPeerAddr.description: This object contain the value of the peer ip address of the Martini VLL PW.

hh3cPwVcMtu.name: hh3cPwVcMtu
hh3cPwVcMtu.description: If not equal zero, the optional Mtu object in the signaling protocol will be sent with this value, representing the locally supported MTU size over the interface (or the virtual interface) associated with the PW. The default value is 1500.

hh3cPwVcCfgType.name: hh3cPwVcCfgType
hh3cPwVcCfgType.description: Indicates the type of the pw: 1: primary; 2: backup; 3: multiPort.

hh3cPwVcInboundLabel.name: hh3cPwVcInboundLabel
hh3cPwVcInboundLabel.description: For Martini VLL, the value will be created by system automatically.

hh3cPwVcOutboundLabel.name: hh3cPwVcOutboundLabel
hh3cPwVcOutboundLabel.description: For Martini VLL, the value will be created by the peer automatically.

hh3cPwVcIfIndex.name: hh3cPwVcIfIndex
hh3cPwVcIfIndex.description: Index of the interface (or the virtual interface) associated with the PW.

hh3cPwVcAcStatus.name: hh3cPwVcAcStatus
hh3cPwVcAcStatus.description: Local AC(Attachment Circuit) status: 1: down; 2: up.

hh3cPwVcStatus.name: hh3cPwVcStatus
hh3cPwVcStatus.description: Indicates the status of the PW in the local node. 1: down; 2: up.

hh3cPwVcRowStatus.name: hh3cPwVcRowStatus
hh3cPwVcRowStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation, deletion and modification of rows, which support active status and CreatAndGo, destroy operation. To create a new row, hh3cPwVcID, hh3cPwVcType, hh3cPwVcPeerAddr hh3cPwVcMtu, hh3cPwVcCfgType and hh3cPwVcIfIndex must be specified.

hh3cPwVcSwitchWtoP.name: hh3cPwVcSwitchWtoP
hh3cPwVcSwitchWtoP.description: This notification is generated when switch from working pw to protect pw happens. The first group of hh3cPwVcID/hh3cPwVcType/hh3cPwVcPeerAddr is parameter of the work PW , and the second group of hh3cPwVcID/hh3cPwVcType/hh3cPwVcPeerAddr is parameter of the protect PW.

hh3cPwVcSwitchPtoW.name: hh3cPwVcSwitchPtoW
hh3cPwVcSwitchPtoW.description: This notification is generated when switch from protect pw to working pw happens. The first group of hh3cPwVcID/h3cPwVcTypehh3cPwVcPeerAddr is parameter of the protect PW , and the second group of hh3cPwVcID/hh3cPwVcType/hh3cPwVcPeerAddr is parameter of the work PW.

hh3cPwVcDown.name: hh3cPwVcDown
hh3cPwVcDown.description: This notification indicates the VC's state changes to down.

hh3cPwVcUp.name: hh3cPwVcUp
hh3cPwVcUp.description: This notification indicates the VC's state changes to up.

hh3cPwVcDeleted.name: hh3cPwVcDeleted
hh3cPwVcDeleted.description: This notification indicates the VC is deleted.
